*+
*  Name:
*     I90_PAR

*  Purpose:
*     Define scalar constants associated with the IRAS satellite and
*     mission.

*  Language:
*     Starlink Fortran 77

*  Description:
*     This module defines scalar parameters holding constants related to
*     the IRAS satellite and mission. It does not define any arrays of
*     constants. Arrays are held in common blocks and are declared in
*     module I90_COM. The values stored in these arrays are initialised
*     within the BLOCK DATA module I90_INIT.

*  Authors:
*     DSB: David Berry (STARLINK)
*     {enter_new_authors_here}

*  History:
*     15-MAY-1992 (DSB):
*        Original version.
*     {enter_changes_here}

*  Bugs:
*     {note_any_bugs_here}

*-
      
*  Constant declarations:

      INTEGER I90__BANDS    ! No. of wavebands.
      INTEGER I90__CBNDS    ! No. of wavebands of CPC images
      INTEGER I90__DETS     ! Total no. of detectors.
      INTEGER I90__FAC      ! IRAS90 facility number (see SUN104 p33).
      INTEGER I90__MAXDT    ! Max. no. of detectors per waveband.
      INTEGER I90__NDEAD    ! No. of dead detectors.
      INTEGER I90__NSMAL    ! No. of small detectors.
      REAL    I90__SMSIZ    ! Cross scan size of largest "small" 
                            ! detector, in arc-mins.
      REAL    I90__SPEED    ! Nominal survey scan speed (arcmins per
                            ! second).

*  Constant values:

      PARAMETER (

     : I90__BANDS = 4,
     : I90__CBNDS = 2,
     : I90__DETS  = 62,
     : I90__FAC   = 1507,
     : I90__MAXDT = 16,
     : I90__NDEAD = 3,
     : I90__NSMAL = 12,
     : I90__SPEED = 3.85,
     : I90__SMSIZ = 3.47 )

*.
